    "recap_headline": "Sacred Heart",
    "recap_text": "Smithfield, R.I. \u2013\nSacred Heart took an early lead behind a first-inning home run from\nPeter Link\n, but Bryant responded with steady offense to walk off with the win.\nRecords\nSacred Heart | 4-14 (3-3 MAAC)\nBryant | 10-8 (2-1 AE)\nTop Performers\nPeter Link\n: 1-2, R, RBI, HR, SB\nWill Rudolph\n: 1-3\nBryan Matuschat\n: 6.0 IP, 13 H, 9 R, 3 SO\nHow It Happened\nSacred Heart jumped out to an early lead in the top of the first inning as\nPeter Link\nlaunched a solo home run to give the Pioneers a 1\u20130 advantage.\nOn the mound,\nBryan Matuschat\nrecorded a strikeout in the first inning, but Bryant responded with a run in the second before adding two more in the third, where Matuschat picked up another strikeout. The Bulldogs continued to build momentum with three runs in the fourth inning.\nMatuschat added another strikeout in the sixth, but Bryant extended its lead with three more runs in the frame. The Bulldogs capped the game in the seventh, scoring two runs to walk it off.\nUp Next\nThe Pioneers return to Smithfield, Rhode Island for a doubleheader against Bryant starting at noon.",
